## What changed

The `issue_autodoc.yml` workflow checks out the private `dotCMS/dotcms-aios` repository as part of its autodoc job. The checkout step previously used the default `GITHUB_TOKEN`, which is scoped only to the `core-workflow-test` repository and cannot read other private org repos. The token is switched to `AUTODOC_TOKEN`, which has org-level read access, allowing the `dotcms-aios` checkout to succeed.

## Risk / watch

Single-line secret reference change in a GitHub Actions workflow. Requires the `AUTODOC_TOKEN` secret to be configured at the repo or org level with read access to `dotCMS/dotcms-aios`; if absent or under-scoped, the autodoc job's checkout step will fail. No application code, database, or API surface is touched.
